## 5. Getting started (summary)

1. Read the quick start guide included in the box.
2. Install or open the app, then follow the on-screen steps.
3. Connect the product to Wi‑Fi when prompted.

If setup fails: factory reset (see § Troubleshooting) or contact support.

---

## 6. Orders, delivery, billing

- **B2C**: card/PayPal payment on the website; PDF invoice by email.
- **B2B**: quote, purchase order, payment net 30 days (approved account).
- **Parcel tracking**: link sent by email on dispatch (carrier depending on country).
- **Returns**: 14-day cooling-off period (new, original packaging); RMA required for after-sales — do not return without an RMA number.

---

## 7. Warranty and after-sales

- **Defect under warranty**: repair or exchange depending on availability.
- **Out of warranty**: normal wear, accidental damage, unauthorized modification → paid quote.
- **Average after-sales time**: varies by request (indicative 10 to 15 business days after receipt).

Replacement parts are supplied only by **authorized after-sales service**.

---

## 8. Quick troubleshooting

| Symptom | Common cause | Action |
|---------|--------------|--------|
| Product not responding | Sleep mode or low battery | Restart; recharge if applicable |
| No longer connects to network | Router/password change | Reconfigure via the app |
| App cannot find product | Product offline or poor network | Check Wi‑Fi; move closer to router |
| Content not up to date | Sync pending | Force sync in the app; restart the product |
| Persistent issue | Variable cause | Contact support with serial number and symptom description |

**Factory reset**: procedure described in the manual or app — clears network configuration and account link, does not delete cloud data (resync required).

